contentrichtext.text: {{Infobox NRHP | name = Zephyrhills Downtown Historic District | image = Zephyrhills Downtown Historic District.jpg | caption = View down 5th Avenue | location = [[Zephyrhills, Florida|Zephyrhills]], [[Florida]] [[United States]] | lat_degrees = 28 | lat_minutes = 14 | lat_seconds = 4 | lat_direction = N | long_degrees = 82 | long_minutes = 10 | long_seconds = 46 | long_direction = W | locmapin = Florida | area = {{convert|840|acre|km2}} | architect = | architecture = | built = 1910 | added = September 27, 2001 | refnum = 95001370<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|version=2010a}}</ref> | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = | architect = | architecture = | refnum = 01001058 }} The '''Zephyrhills Downtown Historic District''' is a historic district in [[Zephyrhills, Florida]]. It is bounded by South Avenue, 9th Avenue, 7th Street and 11th Street, and contains 126 historic buildings. On September 27, 2001, it was added to the [[United States|U.S.]] [[National Register of Historic Places]]. The district includes the [[Capt. Harold B. Jeffries House]] which was built in 1911 and was the home of city founder, Capt. Jeffries. ==Gallery== <gallery> File:Zephyrhills Downtown Hist Dist GAR hall01.jpg|GAR hall File:Zephyrhills Downtown Hist Dist house01.jpg|House in the district File:Zephyrhills Downtown Hist Dist womens club01.jpg|Womens club </gallery> ==References== {{reflist}} ==External links== {{commonscat-inline}} * [http://www.nationalregisterofhistoricplaces.com/FL/Pasco/districts.html Pasco County listings] at [http://www.nationalregisterofhistoricplaces.com National Register of Historic Places] [[Category:Geography of Pasco County, Florida]] [[Category:Historic districts in Florida]] {{Florida-NRHP-district-stub}}
